&nbsp;
Few precedents of such a decision. In fact, during his pontificate never happened. Back in time you arrive at Wojtyla and Ratzinger, although the comparison does not hold: today is a clear case of prevention. In mid-way between 87 and 88, Bergoglio had to accept his despite paying more attention, to expose himself less to weather. In one word: to be concerned. To say it again to the Roman (but the phrase was used years back for another Pope), not to overwhelm.
&nbsp;
