&nbsp;
The exegesis of the communiqué was to conclude that tomorrow and after tomorrow the programme should be followed without any modification. Of course, behind the absence of tonight, there's no malfermous health. Moreover a few hours before, between 16 and 17, Francis attended the ceremony of the Passion, sitting at the right of the main altar of the Basilica. How much he read the formulas of the liturgy, the voice appeared a little roasted, but no more than the days before. Nothing to do with the sudden decision, on Palm Sunday, not to read the homily text.
&nbsp;
