AGI - A patient of the Hospital Brothers Parlapiano di Ribera died in a fire flooded in the medical-cardiology department. The victim is a 50-year-old Romanian. According to the reconstruction of the episode, the man would have taken away the oxygen mask that were administering him and a cigarette would have turned on causing the fire. The spark exploded and a huge fire broke out.
&nbsp;
A wing of the hospital was declared unreasonable. Firemen have tamed the flames in the medical department where there were five hospitalized patients, including the deceased.&nbsp;

